															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1304786&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182401" alt="TL333s" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1304786)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;" >TL333s</a></span> <span class="odate time_1432683131 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">26 May 2015 23:32</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2304241">
									

<p>I can never keep track of shit, so aside from the Hanged King, this was all new to me. I have to hand it to you, I'm gonna point people to this to show them how to get random, otherworldly stuff to sound right.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">And&nbsp;now,&nbsp;if&nbsp;I&nbsp;may,&nbsp;a&nbsp;look&nbsp;at&nbsp;your&nbsp;poetry...</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Cuz&nbsp;it&nbsp;done&nbsp;druv&nbsp;me&nbsp;up&nbsp;tha&nbsp;wizzall</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>Stranger that which is found within,</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I parsed this a number of times as &quot;A stranger that&quot;, but I see what you're getting at. To mend the meter as well as be clearer, try &quot;Stranger yet is found within&quot;, or maybe &quot;still&quot; instead of &quot;yet&quot;.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Here the mad dance without control,</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;The mad dance here without control,&quot; ('The' is a soft syllable and doesn't mess up the meter quite as much at the beginning.)</p>
<blockquote>
<p>And before his glory do we atone,</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This needs help. &quot;Before his glory, we atone&quot; is the best I can do.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>With this, our blood, it is the Hanged King's,<br />
So shall we suffocate upon his puppet-strings.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>These two are a mess, and I could maybe suggest ways to bring them into order. On the other hand, ending with a couplet that's completely nuts, vis-a-vis metrics, actually drives home the chaos and otherworldliness, so I think you could let it stand. However, to make it work, the rest needs to be <em>flawless</em>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

